scopecontent.p:
The portion of the account book that relates to John Randolph Guy's activities as a commission agent records transactions in chronogical order. Entries contain the following information: date of transaction;
name of boat from whom Guy bought goods; name of merchants, businesses, and individuals to whom Guy sold goods; items sold; quantity sold; and cost of goods sold. Items sold include fish, molasses, spices, bacon,
knives, iron pipes, nails, soap, axes, and pianos. Virginia Military Institute was one of Guy's customers.
